cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of drone small cells (DSCs) for wireless communication, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and robotics (cs.RO). The optimization of DSC deployment involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of UAVs for mounting DSCs, which can be considered as a multimedia application (cs.MM) for aerial photography and videography.
